  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0db8\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca \u0da7\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca 332 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Paddy Marketing Board buys 332 MT of paddy",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Agriculture, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera, advised the Paddy Marketing Board to arrange for the purchase of paddy, keeping in mind the objective of giving a good price to the farmers who planted paddy in the yala season.",
        "Accordingly, the paddy marketing board started buying paddy from the last 17 days. The Vee Marketing Board opened 73 stores for the purchase of Vee yesterday.",
        "The warehouses are kept open by reaching the areas that have been cut and are currently being cut. According to Mr. Neil De Alwis, Chairman, 332 metric tons of rice was purchased yesterday, which is the second day of paddy purchase.",
        "There are 29 paddy warehouses in Anuradhapura district and 27 of them are open now. Minister Mahinda Amaraweera says that the government will spend 2000 million rupees to buy paddy."
      ],
